Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
placeSdpGroup(25.10)                                      placeSdpGroup(25.10)

Name
       placeSdpGroup  - Places elements or instances of all defined SDP groups
       in row(s) and column(s) based on user-defined relative placement infor-
       mation

Syntax
       placeSdpGroup

       [-help]

       [-create_inst_group]

       [-deleteOverlap {<cell...>} {<sdp name...>}]

       [-sdpGroups {<name...>}]

       [-noResolveOverlap | [-keepSdpArea]]

       Places elements or instances of all defined SDP groups  in  row(s)  and
       column(s)  based  on  user-defined  relative placement information. The
       placeSdpGroup command:

              * Adjusts the core boundary automatically if the  existing  core
                is not big enough for placing all specified SDPs

              * Resolves  automatically  the  overlaps  on the row/column cell
                list specified in setSdpMode.

              * Honors the alignByPinName SDP constraint for column groups

              * Marks all placed SDP instances to fixed status

              * Places the SDP boundary outside the die area on the right hand
                side if origin information is not defined.

       Before placing SDP groups, you should have:

              * Imported the design

              * Defined SDPs using TCL commands or modified SDPs, as required

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description of the placeSdpGroup command.

              For a detailed description of the command, use the man command:

              man placeSdpGroup.

       -create_inst_group
              Converts failed top sdp groups to instance groups.

              In the 2G flow, the tool supports the conversion of  failed  top
              SDP  groups  to  instGroups by using this parameter. This option
              works only on top SDPs. This means the tool will convert the top
              SDPs to instGroups, irrespective of whether it was the top  SDPs
              or child SDPs that failed.

              The instances in the instance groups are soft_fixed.

       -deleteOverlap {<cell...>} {<sdp name...>}
              Deletes specified physical cells that overlap with all or speci-
              fied SDP groups.

              Note: If you do not specify <sdp name ...>, the specified physi-
              cal cells are removed for all SDPs.

       -keepSdpArea
              Keeps  the  original  SDP structure when resolving overlaps with
              other instances. Use this option if you want to resolve the cell
              overlap by moving the SDP structure instead of changing it.

       -noResolveOverlap
              Ignores overlaps with column/row cells  that  are  specified  in
              setSdpMode.  Use  this  option  to take a look at how the groups
              will be placed before resolving overlaps.

       -sdpGroups {<name...>}
              Places only the specified SDP groups.

Examples
              * The following command places all defined  SDP  groups  without
                removing overlaps:

                placeSdpGroup -noResolveOverlap

